00:12:53.140 --> 00:12:54.599
That's old, old, old Persian.

00:12:54.666 --> 00:12:56.909
It's like maybe 4,000 years ago.

00:12:57.356 --> 00:12:59.576
-Then this is from the old place.
-Yeah.

00:12:59.643 --> 00:13:02.525
-And you guys are gonna redo this?
-Redo the pool.

00:13:03.070 --> 00:13:06.780
Almost every Iranian who's came here
has been able to pretty much crush it.

00:13:06.847 --> 00:13:09.934
My dad came here started out
washing dishes 47 years ago

00:13:10.001 --> 00:13:12.151
and now building houses like this.

00:13:13.380 --> 00:13:14.263
Hey.

00:13:15.247 --> 00:13:17.006
-This is the owner.
-Oh okay.

00:13:17.700 --> 00:13:18.700
-How are you?
-Good.

00:13:18.767 --> 00:13:20.084
-Peter.
-Malek.

00:13:20.151 --> 00:13:22.401
-Malek, nice to meet you.
-Nice to meet you.

00:13:22.468 --> 00:13:24.985
-So you're the owner of the home.
-I sure am.

00:13:25.052 --> 00:13:29.164
And you moved to the US
right before the revolution in 1979.

00:13:29.831 --> 00:13:31.537
What's your take on Arkansas?

00:13:31.604 --> 00:13:34.675
And I just want to say no camera on you,
just on me correct?

00:13:34.742 --> 00:13:35.625
-Yeah.
-Okay.

00:13:35.692 --> 00:13:37.901
I love this state.
I've been in other states.

00:13:37.968 --> 00:13:40.835
I've been in all 50 states.

00:13:40.902 --> 00:13:42.413
None of them matches Arkansas.

00:13:42.480 --> 00:13:44.198
None of them match Arkansas?

00:13:44.265 --> 00:13:47.003
It's big enough but not too many people.

00:13:47.627 --> 00:13:51.097
I drive from here to my office
which is in Redfield.

00:13:51.935 --> 00:13:54.941
30 miles, it takes me 28 minutes.

00:13:55.008 --> 00:13:57.063
-How about the people?
-Very good people.

00:13:57.130 --> 00:13:59.633
Like Persians? Friendly, open?

00:13:59.700 --> 00:14:00.858
-Friendly, open.

00:14:01.665 --> 00:14:05.027
Of course you're gonna find
a little bit prejudice

00:14:05.094 --> 00:14:07.177
and of society too.

00:14:07.244 --> 00:14:10.221
And that's gonna be up to us
to educate them.

00:14:10.788 --> 00:14:14.042
Have you guys had that much of that?
Being Iranian?

00:14:14.551 --> 00:14:17.163
-Yeah. You're gonna have it.
-Little. Very little.

00:14:17.230 --> 00:14:19.644
We are not media what you hear.

00:14:19.711 --> 00:14:20.594
Yeah.

00:14:21.100 --> 00:14:23.887
-Countries is now 3,000 years old.

00:14:24.323 --> 00:14:28.073
Yeah. And I always say
there are people and the government.

00:14:28.641 --> 00:14:30.670
Don't put them in one basket.

00:14:30.737 --> 00:14:33.576
Anywhere in the world.
You know what I mean?

00:14:34.200 --> 00:14:35.510
That's why I went to Iran.

00:14:35.577 --> 00:14:39.172
I made videos of Iran to show Americans
and the world what I saw.

00:14:39.623 --> 00:14:41.174
Some of the nicest people.

00:14:41.241 --> 00:14:44.517
-And all they need,
even the government people out there,

00:14:44.584 --> 00:14:46.066
I've been there a few times.

00:14:46.524 --> 00:14:49.866
All they want you to do,
obey and respect the law.

00:14:50.294 --> 00:14:51.746
Just like in America.

00:14:52.233 --> 00:14:54.009
They want you to respect the law.

00:14:54.495 --> 00:14:58.026
Some countries your freedom is this big.

00:14:58.093 --> 00:15:00.812
And some other countries
the freedom is this big.

00:15:00.879 --> 00:15:02.114
-Okay where's America?

00:15:02.561 --> 00:15:03.444
This big.

00:15:03.511 --> 00:15:05.337
-Where's Iran?
-This big.

00:15:05.404 --> 00:15:06.404
Where's Arkansas?

00:15:06.863 --> 00:15:08.612
-Arkansas is part of America.

00:15:09.139 --> 00:15:12.472
But if you get out of this circle,
you ain't free.

00:15:12.877 --> 00:15:13.760
You're outlaw.

00:15:14.415 --> 00:15:16.474
You have to stay within the circle.

00:15:20.206 --> 00:15:22.697
[Hessam] People's perception
from the outside

00:15:22.764 --> 00:15:25.268
comes from that documentary
Bangin' in Little Rock.

00:15:25.335 --> 00:15:28.539
They think that's all Little Rock is,
like just the hood,

00:15:29.306 --> 00:15:30.409
gang violence,

00:15:31.185 --> 00:15:32.264
crime.

00:15:32.331 --> 00:15:33.919
They don't see these areas.

00:15:34.834 --> 00:15:37.166
In Little Rock
there's something for everybody.

00:15:37.233 --> 00:15:38.992
If you like nature, hiking, biking,

00:15:39.059 --> 00:15:41.440
you come out to this part of the town.

00:15:41.507 --> 00:15:44.210
Okay so we had downtown obviously.

00:15:44.277 --> 00:15:45.543
Well the line.

00:15:45.610 --> 00:15:48.492
We've been north of the line
the whole time today.

00:15:48.932 --> 00:15:50.916
And now we're gonna go south of the line.

00:15:50.983 --> 00:15:53.316
See the other side of the city basically.

00:15:53.383 --> 00:15:56.795
Even though it's been a few
different cities so far. Right?

00:15:56.862 --> 00:15:57.823
Yeah.

00:15:57.890 --> 00:15:58.773
[jazz music]

00:16:19.143 --> 00:16:22.107
[Peter] Alright so just like that.
It totally changes huh?

00:16:22.174 --> 00:16:24.009
[Hessam] South of 630.

00:16:24.077 --> 00:16:26.878
-Some cool old buildings I'm not gonna lie.

00:16:26.949 --> 00:16:29.459
Like there's some nice ones but wow.

00:16:30.369 --> 00:16:33.107
I mean this is like 10 minutes
from where we just were.

00:16:33.174 --> 00:16:35.113
-Just about, yeah.
-Just about 10.

00:16:36.028 --> 00:16:37.604
Some abandoned stuff.

00:16:41.924 --> 00:16:43.182
-Bars on windows.

00:16:44.540 --> 00:16:47.971
I'm sure there's a good community in here
depending on the place right?

00:16:48.038 --> 00:16:49.356
Oh yeah definitely.

00:16:50.460 --> 00:16:52.529
Church not happening anymore.

00:16:53.793 --> 00:16:56.653
It's just such a stark contrast. I mean…

00:16:57.439 --> 00:17:00.388
[Hessam] Back in the day
this was a great part of town.

00:17:00.455 --> 00:17:01.338
Pre-'70s.

00:17:01.850 --> 00:17:04.046
Some nice homes some places are kept well.

00:17:04.113 --> 00:17:05.613
-Yeah.
-Nice lawns.

00:17:06.454 --> 00:17:08.187
So some pride out here.

00:17:08.254 --> 00:17:11.001
Some pride and then
the opposite of pride right there.

00:17:11.068 --> 00:17:12.244
A lot of that stuff.

00:17:13.300 --> 00:17:15.133
Hey I say we should get some food.

00:17:15.577 --> 00:17:16.956
Oh let's ask these guys.

00:17:17.929 --> 00:17:18.812
All right.

00:17:18.879 --> 00:17:21.113
Yeah, I seen that face.
I knew who you were.

00:17:21.180 --> 00:17:22.746
All right. Thank you sir.

00:17:22.813 --> 00:17:26.375
Okay so barbecue.
Where's the best barbecue around here?

00:17:26.442 --> 00:17:29.382
Sim's Barbecue on Roosevelt and Broadway.

00:17:29.449 --> 00:17:30.501
-Broadway.
-Okay.

00:17:30.568 --> 00:17:33.420
Now if you want to take the whole hog,
take the whole hog.

00:17:33.487 --> 00:17:35.063
-Sir what's your name?
-Don.

00:17:35.130 --> 00:17:38.462
-You lived here all your life?
-All my life. I ain't going nowhere.

00:17:38.529 --> 00:17:40.405
All right. How are things these days?

00:17:40.472 --> 00:17:41.913
-Wonderful.
-Wonderful?

00:17:41.980 --> 00:17:44.211
-Yeah. Good friends?
-Prices as high as hell.

00:17:44.278 --> 00:17:47.778
But one day I'm gonna meet old Trump
and ask him for a million dollars.

00:17:47.845 --> 00:17:48.752
I need that. Yeah.

00:17:48.819 --> 00:17:51.333
-Right? Prices are high right now?
-High as hell.

00:17:51.400 --> 00:17:53.459
You're feeling it, gas, food, everything?

00:17:53.526 --> 00:17:56.756
Yeah I am because I travel
between Little Rock and Dallas

00:17:56.823 --> 00:17:58.128
'cause I work in aviation.

00:17:58.195 --> 00:17:59.396
Oh okay.

00:17:59.463 --> 00:18:01.489
-Build private jets.
-No way.

00:18:01.876 --> 00:18:03.947
For Monsters Inc. last week.

00:18:04.014 --> 00:18:05.794
I actually got the pictures.

00:18:05.861 --> 00:18:07.572
-You build private jets?
-Yes I do.

00:18:07.639 --> 00:18:08.553
That's cool.

00:18:08.620 --> 00:18:10.753
-Do you love that work?
-Yeah I do.

00:18:10.820 --> 00:18:14.079
-I love TV. Thank you brother.
-And you're doing a damn good job.

00:18:14.146 --> 00:18:16.036
-Thank you.
-And just stay safe.

00:18:16.103 --> 00:18:18.430
I appreciate it. Thank you guys.

00:18:18.497 --> 00:18:19.194
Thank you.

00:18:19.261 --> 00:18:20.672
[woman] Are you a cameraman?

00:18:20.739 --> 00:18:23.062
Go down there to see him. His name Ronnie.

00:18:23.129 --> 00:18:24.700
-Ronnie?
-Ronnie Sims.

00:18:24.767 --> 00:18:26.503
-Go see Ronnie Sim?
-Yeah.

00:18:26.570 --> 00:18:27.864
-We're doing it.
-Okay.

00:18:28.735 --> 00:18:29.857
Y'all have a good one.

00:18:29.924 --> 00:18:32.150
-[woman] Be careful in the city.
-Be careful?

00:18:32.217 --> 00:18:34.222
-Yes.
-I remember his face too.

00:18:34.289 --> 00:18:35.814
-Me?
-You know this guy?

00:18:36.474 --> 00:18:39.153
-Yeah he look familiar to me.
-[Hessam] I'm from here.

00:18:39.220 --> 00:18:41.820
-[Peter] He's an Iranian model.
-[laughter]

00:18:41.887 --> 00:18:42.770
Is he?

00:18:44.429 --> 00:18:45.379
-Hand model.

00:18:45.446 --> 00:18:48.313
I got a lot of Iranians around here.

00:18:48.380 --> 00:18:50.363
I talk sh*t wherever I go.

00:18:50.430 --> 00:18:52.356
Ain't nothing like life, boy.

00:18:52.423 --> 00:18:53.483
And a smile.

00:18:53.550 --> 00:18:55.729
If you don't smile
you ain't gonna get sh*t.

00:18:55.796 --> 00:18:57.526
Give us some… Give us some wisdom.

00:18:57.593 --> 00:18:59.062
Life… Smile.

00:18:59.129 --> 00:19:02.953
-What do you wanna tell the young people?
-Young people stay alive.

00:19:03.020 --> 00:19:06.732
'Cause goddammit y'all leaving us alone
with all these young gals.

00:19:06.799 --> 00:19:08.215
Live old, die young.

00:19:09.002 --> 00:19:10.148
They dying young.

00:19:10.665 --> 00:19:12.873
-They're dying young.
-They're dying young?

00:19:12.940 --> 00:19:16.308
Leaving their kids behind
for me to take care of.

00:19:16.790 --> 00:19:18.580
So just tell them I'mma take care.

00:19:18.647 --> 00:19:19.573
How old are you?

00:19:19.640 --> 00:19:22.170
67 and still living.

00:19:22.237 --> 00:19:25.169
-You got a wife?
-Yeah. Right there.

00:19:25.979 --> 00:19:27.391
And one down the street.

00:19:27.458 --> 00:19:28.341
[laughter]

00:19:29.465 --> 00:19:32.476
-Did you hear what I said?
-I heard you loud and clear.

00:19:32.543 --> 00:19:34.666
Right there. And one down the street.

00:19:34.733 --> 00:19:35.933
They gon' see it.

00:19:36.000 --> 00:19:38.146
You 'bout to be put out of business.

00:19:38.213 --> 00:19:39.741
It's so much more interesting.

00:19:39.808 --> 00:19:42.771
We were just in
the most boring neighborhood in town.

00:19:42.838 --> 00:19:45.488
-What hood you was in?
-What was we just went through?

00:19:45.555 --> 00:19:47.566
We just came through from John Barrow.

00:19:47.633 --> 00:19:48.990
Oh that's bored over there.

00:19:49.057 --> 00:19:51.743
There's no one like you
with flavor over there.

00:19:51.810 --> 00:19:54.281
-Sh*t.
-I need the jokes. I need the humor.

00:19:54.847 --> 00:19:56.823
-Life is the humor.
-It is huh?

00:19:56.890 --> 00:20:01.165
Yeah, enjoy yourself. You ain't got a smile
on your face, something wrong with you.

00:20:01.232 --> 00:20:02.115
Always smile.

00:20:02.870 --> 00:20:04.041
You go a long damn way.

00:20:04.108 --> 00:20:06.343
You see this right here? Monsters Inc.

00:20:07.491 --> 00:20:08.374
You see that?

00:20:08.441 --> 00:20:10.212
-You're building those?
-Yeah.

00:20:10.279 --> 00:20:12.338
-Good for you.
-That's Monsters Inc.

00:20:12.941 --> 00:20:15.891
So you're one of the crew members
building the actual plane?

00:20:15.958 --> 00:20:16.841
Yes.

00:20:17.292 --> 00:20:19.358
How does that feel when it's done?

00:20:19.425 --> 00:20:22.454
It's really great.
Like the ceremony is really nice.

00:20:22.521 --> 00:20:23.580
It's really great.

00:20:24.827 --> 00:20:27.377
I like to kind of represent
for the women

00:20:27.829 --> 00:20:30.009
in aviation
because it's not a lot of women.

00:20:30.076 --> 00:20:31.787
It's like a male dominated field.

00:20:31.854 --> 00:20:34.972
So I just want women
to just keep pushing to be great.

00:20:35.665 --> 00:20:37.517
-How'd you get into building planes?

00:20:37.584 --> 00:20:39.421
Well it actually started on Indeed.

00:20:39.488 --> 00:20:43.889
I applied and I started working at
a big one we have here called Falcon Jet.

00:20:44.464 --> 00:20:47.358
They found me from Dallas
and they paid me a per diem

00:20:47.425 --> 00:20:49.953
to go down there to work
because of my skill.

00:20:50.020 --> 00:20:52.516
-It was nice to meet you.
-You too. Thank you.

00:20:54.845 --> 00:20:56.835
[Peter] So Sim's BBQ is closed?

00:20:56.902 --> 00:20:58.353
[Hessam] Sim's BBQ is closed.

00:20:58.420 --> 00:21:00.538
This is the next best thing I think.

00:21:02.860 --> 00:21:04.860
[man] Just five dollars right now.

00:21:05.304 --> 00:21:07.849
[Peter] Hot dogs three pork chops five.

00:21:08.330 --> 00:21:10.173
-I'll do a hot dog.
-Hot dog.

00:21:10.860 --> 00:21:12.472
-Hot dog?
-Two hot dogs.

00:21:12.852 --> 00:21:15.672
He gon' have to get it.
All right. What's your name boss?

00:21:15.739 --> 00:21:16.925
-E.
-E, Peter.

00:21:17.580 --> 00:21:19.661
So you just riding around in the hoods?

00:21:19.728 --> 00:21:22.009
-With a camera?
-Yeah. Everywhere.

00:21:22.076 --> 00:21:23.135
Not just the hood.

00:21:24.036 --> 00:21:25.713
I want to show all sides of the city.

00:21:25.780 --> 00:21:27.616
I like your courage, man.

00:21:27.683 --> 00:21:29.742
-Courage?
-I like your courage, man.

00:21:30.233 --> 00:21:33.012
But if you go to Louisiana
don't do that man.

00:21:33.564 --> 00:21:36.496
-Don't do this in Louisiana?
-Don't do that in New Orleans.

00:21:36.563 --> 00:21:38.464
I have done it in New Orleans.

00:21:38.531 --> 00:21:41.185
-Where you was at?
-9th Ward. I've been all over.

00:21:41.252 --> 00:21:42.135
I promise.

00:21:42.660 --> 00:21:44.796
-It's better here than New Orleans?
-Yes.

00:21:44.863 --> 00:21:47.092
-People nicer or what?
-They nicer here.

00:21:48.012 --> 00:21:49.996
They just killed the bus driver

00:21:50.063 --> 00:21:52.271
in front of 76 people.

00:21:52.338 --> 00:21:53.460
They doing crazy sh*t.

00:21:53.527 --> 00:21:54.704
-In New Orleans?

00:21:56.364 --> 00:21:58.717
On the river. Dude killed the bus driver.

00:21:59.881 --> 00:22:03.587
-Okay tell me about Little Rock.
How are things here these days?

00:22:04.371 --> 00:22:07.866
Little Rock done got a lot better man.
Back in the '90s it was worse.

00:22:07.933 --> 00:22:10.109
-So what are you wanting?
-Two hot dogs.

00:22:10.616 --> 00:22:11.844
So it's gotten better?

00:22:11.911 --> 00:22:13.760
Oh yeah, 100% better.

00:22:14.213 --> 00:22:17.500
It's a nice place to live at now
compared to how it was back then.

00:22:17.580 --> 00:22:20.047
-So when the movie came out.
-Bangin' in Little Rock?

00:22:20.114 --> 00:22:22.872
-Yeah. That was mid '90s.

00:22:22.939 --> 00:22:25.870
But that's what it was at it's worst right?

00:22:25.937 --> 00:22:28.540
-It ain't nothing like that no more.
-Okay.

00:22:28.607 --> 00:22:30.413
They tried to get it back like that.

00:22:30.972 --> 00:22:33.593
So if I walked around
these streets solo mission

00:22:33.660 --> 00:22:35.132
would I have a problem or no?

00:22:35.199 --> 00:22:37.514
-Yeah you can.
-You can have a problem.

00:22:37.985 --> 00:22:40.532
You can but basically it's different

00:22:40.599 --> 00:22:43.193
like than from New Orleans now.

00:22:43.260 --> 00:22:46.850
Because a Caucasian guy
couldn't just walk in any hood.

00:22:46.917 --> 00:22:49.885
But since Katrina it's a whole lot better.

00:22:49.952 --> 00:22:50.952
-In New Orleans?
-Yes

00:22:51.019 --> 00:22:53.860
You know, I never dealt with
Caucasian people

00:22:54.367 --> 00:22:55.896
until I moved to Arkansas.

00:22:56.411 --> 00:22:57.294
-Seriously?

00:22:57.361 --> 00:23:00.185
Yes I never even seen
a Caucasian woman pregnant.

00:23:00.798 --> 00:23:02.471
-Come on.
-I promise you.

00:23:02.538 --> 00:23:06.883
If you see Caucasian
in my neighborhood it was drugs.

00:23:07.391 --> 00:23:10.705
-That's a nice grill, man.
-Thank you man.

00:23:11.725 --> 00:23:14.304
That's when they made them well.
Just thick metal.

00:23:15.164 --> 00:23:16.301
Oh, look at that.

00:23:16.368 --> 00:23:17.387
-[laughs]

00:23:17.454 --> 00:23:18.708
-Here we go.

00:23:18.775 --> 00:23:22.125
-What's the name of the business?
Or just stop at the street corner?

00:23:22.192 --> 00:23:23.672
What is it, Marshall?

00:23:23.739 --> 00:23:25.897
Marshall and Asher.

00:23:25.970 --> 00:23:27.992
-That's Wright Avenue.
-Wright Avenue.

00:23:28.059 --> 00:23:28.942
Okay.

00:23:29.010 --> 00:23:31.188
You want mustard and barbecue sauce?

00:23:31.255 --> 00:23:32.685
Mustard barbecue sauce?

00:23:33.868 --> 00:23:35.207
He likes barbecue.

00:23:35.274 --> 00:23:37.737
We got the nice people over there. We just…

00:23:38.268 --> 00:23:40.873
-I'll go check them out.
-Go check them out.

00:23:41.478 --> 00:23:43.724
They got some good food over there.

00:23:44.601 --> 00:23:46.474
African food, Nigerian.

00:23:48.241 --> 00:23:49.300
Can you hold this?

00:23:50.029 --> 00:23:50.912
What you got?

00:23:51.550 --> 00:23:53.910
-I want to show your dogs here.
-We got my guy.

00:23:53.977 --> 00:23:55.156
That's a $3 dog.

00:23:55.223 --> 00:23:57.018
In 2026

00:23:57.578 --> 00:23:59.637
you can't do much better on prices.

00:24:00.070 --> 00:24:01.758
-Than $3 right?
-Yeah.

00:24:03.200 --> 00:24:05.124
But I wish you well out here man.

00:24:05.191 --> 00:24:06.485
-Thank you.
-All right.

00:24:07.496 --> 00:24:09.396
I haven't had a dog in like 10 years.

00:24:09.463 --> 00:24:10.863
-Why not?
-It's good.

00:24:10.930 --> 00:24:11.813
[laughter]

00:24:12.873 --> 00:24:15.226
I just haven't done dogs but it's good.

00:24:20.790 --> 00:24:22.420
Do you work here too, sir?

00:24:22.487 --> 00:24:24.247
No. He doesn't work here.

00:24:24.314 --> 00:24:26.735
-I'm a customer.
-He's a customer.

00:24:26.802 --> 00:24:28.862
He's a brother. He's a friend.

00:24:28.929 --> 00:24:30.430
We grew up in this community.

00:24:30.497 --> 00:24:31.963
This is our community.

00:24:32.034 --> 00:24:33.669
We been here all our lives.

00:24:33.736 --> 00:24:36.246
-We moved away, come back.
-Okay.

00:24:36.313 --> 00:24:39.573
For the most part this is our neighborhood,
where we come from.

00:24:39.640 --> 00:24:43.164
I sell health and wellness,
skin care, cosmetics.

00:24:43.550 --> 00:24:46.465
I attend the Islamic center
across the street.

00:24:46.532 --> 00:24:48.833
My mother and my father were Muslims.

00:24:48.900 --> 00:24:50.436
And then we have Afro Bites.

00:24:50.503 --> 00:24:53.993
We're all one community
under this umbrella of the Islamic center.

00:24:54.060 --> 00:24:56.271
-Salamu alaykum.
-Wa alaikum as-salam.

00:24:56.338 --> 00:24:57.293
[Arabic]

00:24:57.360 --> 00:24:59.672
You know all the Muslim countries
I've been to.

00:24:59.739 --> 00:25:02.143
-First, hospitality is fantastic.
-For sure.

00:25:02.210 --> 00:25:03.567
Secondly, I like Ramadan.

00:25:03.634 --> 00:25:05.323
I like the principles of Ramadan.

00:25:05.390 --> 00:25:07.233
Yeah, it's discipline.

00:25:07.300 --> 00:25:10.594
-It's discipline and it teaches gratitude.
-Yep.

00:25:10.661 --> 00:25:14.683
And when you go without and then you
get the thing again it feels amazing.

00:25:14.750 --> 00:25:18.239
What do you focus on?
That's what you got to look at.

00:25:18.306 --> 00:25:20.284
-With life you mean?
-Yeah, with life.

00:25:20.351 --> 00:25:22.785
Are you always focused on what's negative?

00:25:22.852 --> 00:25:24.911
Are you paying attention to that more?

00:25:24.978 --> 00:25:27.137
Are you paying attention
to positive things?

00:25:27.204 --> 00:25:29.019
Being grateful for what you do have.

00:25:29.086 --> 00:25:31.659
So then you will be able to receive more.

00:25:31.726 --> 00:25:33.335
It's your focus. It's your mind.

00:25:33.402 --> 00:25:35.998
-Have you always been like that?
-No. I haven't.

00:25:36.065 --> 00:25:38.154
For me it was a growing thing.

00:25:38.611 --> 00:25:40.759
It was experiencing life.

00:25:40.826 --> 00:25:42.883
Different places. Different people.

00:25:42.950 --> 00:25:46.038
But coming back to my ground roots.

00:25:46.105 --> 00:25:49.152
We go out into the world
and we be like, "Ooh, the world."

00:25:49.219 --> 00:25:50.102
Right.

00:25:50.169 --> 00:25:52.189
And you start being a part of the world.

00:25:52.256 --> 00:25:55.628
And my mom used to tell me
don't be of the world.

00:25:56.056 --> 00:25:58.200
-And now I understand what she said.
-Okay.

00:25:58.267 --> 00:26:00.189
About don't be a part of the world.

00:26:00.256 --> 00:26:01.432
Make your own world.

00:26:02.405 --> 00:26:05.464
Because the world that you see
is really not reality.

00:26:06.615 --> 00:26:07.498
It's made up.

00:26:08.089 --> 00:26:10.471
Because the world
is really what's in your mind.

00:26:10.538 --> 00:26:14.005
What you believe about yourself.
So you can rewrite your story.

00:26:14.072 --> 00:26:16.489
You can create the world that you want.

00:26:16.556 --> 00:26:20.137
Just by seeing it in your mind
and doing the things outside

00:26:21.422 --> 00:26:23.766
to cultivate who you want to be.

00:26:24.907 --> 00:26:27.607
You gotta pray, speak, and ask

00:26:28.299 --> 00:26:30.410
God for the things that you want.

00:26:30.914 --> 00:26:32.620
And do your part in the work.

00:26:33.170 --> 00:26:36.490
'Cause he will open doors
and bring you the right people

00:26:36.557 --> 00:26:38.315
to bring that life into the world.

00:26:38.382 --> 00:26:41.292
-And that's worked for you?
-Yeah. It really has. Honestly.

00:26:41.359 --> 00:26:43.139
It really has. It's a mindset.

00:26:43.206 --> 00:26:46.242
I don't watch TV.
I don't focus on negative things.

00:26:46.309 --> 00:26:47.604
Even when things happen

00:26:47.671 --> 00:26:51.043
I still look at it like
it was the reason why that happened.

00:26:51.572 --> 00:26:53.129
So it really wasn't negative.

00:26:53.196 --> 00:26:56.954
It may have been a great thing
that I didn't go into that area.

00:26:57.028 --> 00:26:59.924
I didn't receive
that acknowledgment or whatever

00:26:59.991 --> 00:27:01.579
because I may not be ready.

00:27:01.994 --> 00:27:04.472
I may need to do
a little bit more work on myself.

00:27:04.539 --> 00:27:06.721
-What age did you
come into this transition?

00:27:06.788 --> 00:27:09.441
Oh my God. How old am I?

00:27:09.928 --> 00:27:12.352
In my thirties. When I had my daughter.

00:27:12.419 --> 00:27:14.772
It came a little bit before I had her.

00:27:14.839 --> 00:27:16.848
But she really just propelled me.

00:27:16.915 --> 00:27:18.187
She pushed me.

00:27:18.254 --> 00:27:20.749
Because now I have somebody
looking at me.

00:27:20.816 --> 00:27:23.322
I have somebody
that I'm responsible for.

00:27:23.389 --> 00:27:26.962
What they see, what they eat,
how they live, how they perceive life.

00:27:27.029 --> 00:27:28.551
That's my responsibility.

00:27:28.999 --> 00:27:31.288
That's not nobody else's responsibility.

00:27:31.355 --> 00:27:34.885
So if I don't change how I move
and the things that I do

00:27:34.952 --> 00:27:37.305
then she's just gonna pick up on the BS.

00:27:38.378 --> 00:27:41.328
You have to become
a whole new person when you become a mom.

00:27:41.395 --> 00:27:43.845
I can't be out
doing the things that I used to do

00:27:43.912 --> 00:27:45.794
in my young age when I was free.

00:27:46.414 --> 00:27:49.887
But now I have someone
that's looking at me as an example.

00:27:49.954 --> 00:27:51.958
And so I have to step up to the plate.

00:27:52.417 --> 00:27:54.627
It ain't easy but once you do it

00:27:54.694 --> 00:27:58.150
the rewards is when she's older
and how she's moving her life.

00:27:58.654 --> 00:28:00.558
And the impact that I had on her.

00:28:00.625 --> 00:28:02.816
And then she will carry that vision,

00:28:03.238 --> 00:28:05.626
those ideas, into her everyday life.

00:28:05.693 --> 00:28:08.215
You know what I'm saying?
So it's really a mindset.

00:28:08.282 --> 00:28:11.400
It's all in your mind
'cause God resides in the heart.

00:28:11.959 --> 00:28:14.732
So once you clean up your insides
and how you think,

00:28:14.799 --> 00:28:17.140
God can really move in your life.

00:28:17.698 --> 00:28:20.413
Because he's in there waiting
for us to realize.

00:28:20.480 --> 00:28:24.765
He in here and he's not something
that you can find outside.

00:28:25.659 --> 00:28:28.273
Because He already resides in the heart.
He made you.

00:28:28.340 --> 00:28:30.859
A bird is always going to do bird duties.

00:28:30.926 --> 00:28:33.528
It knows what it's supposed to do.
That's his nature.

00:28:33.595 --> 00:28:36.348
But you as a human being, a living soul,

00:28:36.415 --> 00:28:37.943
God gave you a choice.

00:28:38.010 --> 00:28:40.010
He gave you a choice to be an alcoholic.

00:28:40.077 --> 00:28:42.294
'Cause you choose.
You said you wanted to be.

00:28:42.361 --> 00:28:45.289
You let that be
your main factor for your life.

00:28:45.356 --> 00:28:48.211
So now you're an alcoholic.
Because you choose to do that.

00:28:48.278 --> 00:28:51.097
You don't have the
strength or the ability to say

00:28:51.164 --> 00:28:52.984
I don't want to do this no more.

00:28:53.051 --> 00:28:55.286
Whatever it takes I'm not gonna drink.

00:28:56.454 --> 00:28:58.070
That has to be a discipline.

00:28:58.137 --> 00:28:59.438
That has to be a muscle.

00:28:59.505 --> 00:29:00.700
That has to be a want.

00:29:01.120 --> 00:29:02.649
You have to want to do it.

00:29:03.225 --> 00:29:06.375
You may need to do something,
that don't mean you want to do it.

00:29:06.442 --> 00:29:09.003
Your life is what you made it
because you chose.

00:29:09.070 --> 00:29:11.973
Just like you chose to be with a guy.

00:29:12.040 --> 00:29:13.385
He wasn't a good guy.

00:29:13.938 --> 00:29:15.161
Now you got a baby.

00:29:15.228 --> 00:29:16.111
Now you mad.

00:29:16.955 --> 00:29:20.165
But you chose to be with that individual.
Same thing for a woman.

00:29:20.232 --> 00:29:22.673
-So you're saying self responsibility?
-Yes!

00:29:22.741 --> 00:29:24.629
Nobody's responsible for you.

00:29:24.696 --> 00:29:27.179
Nobody can change your condition but you.

00:29:27.246 --> 00:29:29.475
-And it's empowering
to know that and realize

00:29:29.542 --> 00:29:31.446
you have more control than you think.

00:29:31.513 --> 00:29:34.056
You have all the control.
God has the control.

00:29:34.129 --> 00:29:36.149
But he has given you the power

00:29:36.592 --> 00:29:38.842
to have control to choose

00:29:39.420 --> 00:29:40.849
what you're gonna do.

00:29:40.916 --> 00:29:43.437
Are you gonna go out
and visit the club today?

00:29:43.504 --> 00:29:46.776
Are you gonna work on that new business
that you want to start?

00:29:46.843 --> 00:29:50.376
You can't keep doing the same thing
over and over again

00:29:50.443 --> 00:29:52.643
and think
you're gonna get different results.

00:29:52.710 --> 00:29:55.475
You're not.
You're just gonna get the same sh*t.

00:30:07.411 --> 00:30:10.714
So we're on our way to
the Latino side of Southwest Little Rock.

00:30:10.781 --> 00:30:12.261
Geyer Springs, Baseline.

00:30:14.141 --> 00:30:16.981
So a lot of these shopping centers were
pretty much empty

00:30:17.048 --> 00:30:18.808
up until 15 years ago.

00:30:18.875 --> 00:30:21.718
And now you see a lot of Latino businesses.

00:30:21.785 --> 00:30:24.093
-Oh let's stop at a little drink place.

00:30:24.859 --> 00:30:28.682
Yeah wow. That's like we went to
another country immediately.

00:30:28.749 --> 00:30:29.690
[chuckles] Yeah.

00:30:42.251 --> 00:30:43.898
The old coconut, some fruit.

00:30:45.853 --> 00:30:46.736
Thank you, sir.

00:30:48.706 --> 00:30:49.589
Cheers.

00:30:49.656 --> 00:30:51.209
[man speaking Spanish]

00:30:52.420 --> 00:30:54.509
[man] [Spanish] But it's something else.

00:30:54.576 --> 00:30:56.933
[Peter] I look like a cop.
I can't help it, man.

00:30:57.000 --> 00:30:59.059
Tell them I can't help it.
[Spanish]

00:31:00.293 --> 00:31:02.393
I made a bunch of videos in Mexico.

00:31:02.460 --> 00:31:04.147
Okay nice. All right, brother.

00:31:04.214 --> 00:31:07.247
-Do you live around here, bro?
-No.

00:31:07.314 --> 00:31:09.246
-Okay.
-Just came for this.

00:31:09.313 --> 00:31:10.553
Nice. Thank you.

00:31:13.090 --> 00:31:15.296
You want a drink or do you want the fruit?

00:31:15.363 --> 00:31:16.653
-I really like the taro.

00:31:16.720 --> 00:31:17.713
-Okay, taro.

00:31:19.160 --> 00:31:20.870
Thank you brother. Appreciate it.

00:31:20.937 --> 00:31:21.820
Hasta luego.

00:31:24.580 --> 00:31:28.832
The crime here is a lot less
than the other side that we were just on.

00:31:28.899 --> 00:31:29.782
-Mm-hmm.

00:31:29.849 --> 00:31:31.476
And ever since the past 10 years

00:31:31.543 --> 00:31:35.196
that's been more Latino businesses
coming here it's gotten a lot better

00:31:35.263 --> 00:31:36.692
than what it was before.

00:31:36.759 --> 00:31:37.983
-What was it before?

00:31:38.050 --> 00:31:39.811
-Just like where we were at.
-Okay.

00:31:40.824 --> 00:31:45.312
So like any city, different groups
are always getting moved around?

00:31:45.379 --> 00:31:46.262
Yeah.

00:31:47.127 --> 00:31:50.027
People that were here
living before where did they move?

00:31:50.094 --> 00:31:52.356
Those who had money
moved to West Little Rock.

00:31:52.423 --> 00:31:53.306
Okay.

00:31:53.373 --> 00:31:56.951
And those who didn't,
they moved to the outskirts

00:31:57.018 --> 00:31:59.297
like East End and those type of areas.

00:31:59.364 --> 00:32:01.884
Hensley,
where that one guy was we just met.

00:32:01.951 --> 00:32:05.485
Is there beef here? Is there friction
in that situation or not really?

00:32:05.552 --> 00:32:06.616
-Not really.

00:32:06.683 --> 00:32:09.087
-You don't really see it?
-It's pretty laid back.

00:32:09.154 --> 00:32:10.273
-It's laid back?
-Yeah.

00:32:10.340 --> 00:32:12.263
They're pretty scared of ICE.

00:32:12.330 --> 00:32:15.874
They just go home, go to work,
and if they gotta go somewhere,

00:32:15.941 --> 00:32:19.633
they'll go in like a pair,
or two, or three, just to be safe.

00:32:20.267 --> 00:32:21.579
-What do you mean be safe?

00:32:21.646 --> 00:32:23.666
ICE is gonna get all of them then right?

00:32:23.733 --> 00:32:25.125
Well not exactly.

00:32:25.192 --> 00:32:27.038
If one of them gets got

00:32:27.105 --> 00:32:30.014
then the others would know about it quicker

00:32:30.081 --> 00:32:31.669
'cause you run that risk of

00:32:32.213 --> 00:32:34.899
someone gets taken
and you just never hear about it.

00:32:34.966 --> 00:32:36.054
You would never know.

00:32:36.121 --> 00:32:39.844
-Okay. The people you know out here,
the ones that don't have papers,

00:32:39.911 --> 00:32:41.634
they're like laying really low.

00:32:41.701 --> 00:32:43.536
Oh yeah, they're laying pretty low.

00:32:44.079 --> 00:32:48.503
-So what percentage
do you think is legal versus illegal here?

00:32:48.570 --> 00:32:49.684
-Legal?
-Yeah.

00:32:50.251 --> 00:32:53.159
Maybe like 10, 15%.

00:32:53.705 --> 00:32:54.726
-Is legal?!

00:32:54.793 --> 00:32:55.785
Legal yeah.

00:32:55.852 --> 00:32:59.072
Maybe 10% of them
have some type of papers or…

00:32:59.758 --> 00:33:01.839
-That's a big number man.

00:33:01.906 --> 00:33:02.789
Yeah.

00:33:02.856 --> 00:33:04.522
-You really think it's that?

00:33:04.589 --> 00:33:06.749
That's my personal opinion.

00:33:06.816 --> 00:33:08.882
-Yeah there's no way of knowing for sure.

00:33:08.949 --> 00:33:11.776
There's no way of knowing for sure
but you know based on…

00:33:11.843 --> 00:33:15.092
-You'd say in this immediate area
that's what the story is?

00:33:15.159 --> 00:33:16.310
Oh yeah, definitely.

00:33:16.377 --> 00:33:18.793
-Wow. This is a mega trailer park.

00:33:18.860 --> 00:33:20.473
-It's almost all Latino.

00:33:21.373 --> 00:33:23.143
A lot of them that are legal,

00:33:23.210 --> 00:33:26.029
they're from DACA or they were born here.

00:33:26.500 --> 00:33:30.146
They were able to apply for their parents,
that type of deal.

00:33:30.668 --> 00:33:35.039
-So has the Hispanic community grown a lot
in the last 10 years here?

00:33:35.106 --> 00:33:36.180
-Definitely yes.

00:33:36.247 --> 00:33:37.253
-Big time?
-Yes.

00:33:37.708 --> 00:33:39.685
Absolutely nobody outside?

00:33:39.752 --> 00:33:42.029
-Before maybe four or five years ago

00:33:42.096 --> 00:33:45.487
you'd have some people hanging out
barbecuing playing some music.

00:33:46.005 --> 00:33:49.021
Now they're just staying in,
hanging out inside.

00:33:49.464 --> 00:33:51.560
-Okay so tough question for you. Ready?

00:33:52.130 --> 00:33:54.548
-You have the magic wand.
-Okay.

00:33:54.615 --> 00:33:57.053
How do you fix this immigration issue?

00:33:57.120 --> 00:33:58.706
Like where we're at right now.

00:33:58.773 --> 00:34:00.655
-Where we're at right now?
-Yeah.

00:34:01.186 --> 00:34:02.598
Give me your simple fix.

00:34:04.170 --> 00:34:08.402
Give everybody a social security
and a work permit.

00:34:09.620 --> 00:34:10.503
For how long?

00:34:11.423 --> 00:34:13.698
For however long would be reasonable.

00:34:13.765 --> 00:34:16.963
Maybe 5 years, 10 years, you can renew it.

00:34:17.389 --> 00:34:18.990
So they crossed illegally.

00:34:21.086 --> 00:34:22.119
Just let that go?

00:34:22.600 --> 00:34:23.773
I mean they're here.

00:34:23.840 --> 00:34:26.303
They're here,
they're part of the workforce.

00:34:26.370 --> 00:34:29.718
Yeah, the reality is
if everyone gets deported

00:34:29.785 --> 00:34:34.567
good luck building homes these days,
or landscaping, or kitchens.

00:34:35.300 --> 00:34:37.201
I do believe in following the law.

00:34:37.671 --> 00:34:40.310
It was really murky
on the border for a while.

00:34:40.377 --> 00:34:42.253
Where they're getting asylum claims.

00:34:42.320 --> 00:34:44.622
When they were illegitimate asylum claims?

00:34:44.689 --> 00:34:47.230
But everyone knew the story
and how to play it.

00:34:47.774 --> 00:34:50.846
And it seems like the government
incentivized it almost.

00:34:50.913 --> 00:34:52.409
At least when I was there.

00:34:52.884 --> 00:34:55.831
Customs Border Protection guys
had to actually

00:34:56.291 --> 00:34:58.329
process people.

00:34:58.396 --> 00:35:01.903
Now there were rules.
Other than Mexicans couldn't get up here.

00:35:01.970 --> 00:35:05.444
That's what's interesting.
They would send Mexicans back immediately.

00:35:05.511 --> 00:35:08.317
But if you're from Colombia
you're getting in.

00:35:08.384 --> 00:35:09.973
-Wow.
-Yeah it was wild.

00:35:10.040 --> 00:35:13.024
And the rules change
and it's really murky and confusing.

00:35:13.091 --> 00:35:15.209
It's a complicated topic all around.

00:35:18.887 --> 00:35:22.648
So the city of Little Rock
has this program for homeless people

00:35:22.715 --> 00:35:24.498
where they provide them with a job.

00:35:24.565 --> 00:35:27.993
-Like that guy standing right there?
-Pretty much.

00:35:28.060 --> 00:35:30.484
And they'll pay them
like 15 or 16 bucks an hour

00:35:30.551 --> 00:35:33.036
to clean up the city, pick up trash.

00:35:33.707 --> 00:35:37.519
There's actually been quite a few people
that have entered into that program.

00:35:37.586 --> 00:35:40.887
And there was one in the news last year
that he entered the program

00:35:40.954 --> 00:35:43.363
and he was able to buy his own house.

00:35:43.883 --> 00:35:44.799
You know?

00:35:46.019 --> 00:35:47.979
-This is a college area?
-Yeah.

00:35:49.143 --> 00:35:51.843
You wanted to show this
'cause there's students coming?

00:35:51.910 --> 00:35:53.526
Yeah. There's a lot of students.

00:35:53.593 --> 00:35:55.646
-They rent out here.
-You rent out here?

00:35:55.713 --> 00:35:57.173
-[man] I own.
-You own?

00:35:57.240 --> 00:35:59.032
Yeah. Just got this guy.

00:35:59.490 --> 00:36:01.795
Had it about a year and a half now.
It's great.

00:36:01.862 --> 00:36:04.329
Neighborhood's cool. Neighbors are awesome.

00:36:04.396 --> 00:36:06.663
This guy's from Serbia.

00:36:06.730 --> 00:36:08.806
Jose's from Mexico. We're from Japan.

00:36:08.873 --> 00:36:10.073
-No way.
-Yeah. For real.

00:36:10.140 --> 00:36:11.571
It's very diverse.

00:36:11.638 --> 00:36:14.781
-So it's like university rentals
and then a few owners?

00:36:14.848 --> 00:36:17.945
Yeah. It's definitely
a very rental neighborhood.

00:36:18.012 --> 00:36:19.873
-Being close to the university.
-Okay.

00:36:19.940 --> 00:36:22.990
Found an awesome house.
My wife and I, this is our first home.

00:36:23.057 --> 00:36:24.604
-Congrats man.
-Yeah man.

00:36:25.105 --> 00:36:26.236
How old are you?

00:36:26.303 --> 00:36:27.623
Just turned 37.

00:36:27.690 --> 00:36:31.156
-If you don't mind me asking,
Little Rock, what's something like this?

00:36:31.223 --> 00:36:33.521
We got this one for $184.

00:36:34.120 --> 00:36:35.186
1,500 square feet.

00:36:35.253 --> 00:36:38.984
I feel like that's probably
pretty hard to find in a lot of places.

00:36:39.051 --> 00:36:40.950
-That is sweet, $184.
-Yeah.

00:36:41.410 --> 00:36:44.505
One bought two weeks ago.
Some friends of mine got a new house

00:36:44.572 --> 00:36:47.399
and then got some friends
that are about to get one too.

00:36:47.466 --> 00:36:49.372
So it's definitely attainable here

00:36:49.439 --> 00:36:52.313
for the average person
to be able to live the dream.

00:36:52.380 --> 00:36:53.586
-What's your work?

00:36:53.653 --> 00:36:54.594
I'm a bartender.

00:36:55.095 --> 00:36:57.752
So I'm not even
like a salary gig or anything.

00:36:57.819 --> 00:37:00.344
I just enjoy what I do
in the hospitality industry.

00:37:00.411 --> 00:37:01.294
-Nice.

00:37:01.361 --> 00:37:04.319
My wife does legal assistant work.

00:37:04.386 --> 00:37:06.306
We both were in the industry for years

00:37:06.373 --> 00:37:09.386
and then just kind of
were able to make this happen.

00:37:09.453 --> 00:37:11.168
-So it's American dream…

00:37:11.235 --> 00:37:13.533
-…still possible in Little Rock?
-For sure.

00:37:13.600 --> 00:37:16.810
Yeah love to see
what $184 buys in Little Rock.

00:37:16.877 --> 00:37:18.050
-Yeah come check it out.

00:37:18.117 --> 00:37:19.683
-Did you do a lot of work to it?

00:37:19.750 --> 00:37:21.697
No. So the family that lived here

00:37:21.764 --> 00:37:24.364
was here for 28 years
and they took great care of it.

00:37:24.431 --> 00:37:25.314
-Okay.

00:37:25.381 --> 00:37:27.492
It was pretty much move in ready.

00:37:27.559 --> 00:37:29.670
My wife painted the door,
painted the kitchen.

00:37:30.430 --> 00:37:32.783
Got some puppies but they're super chill.

00:37:33.891 --> 00:37:35.838
This guy's four and a half months old.

00:37:35.905 --> 00:37:37.083
-How you doing?
-Hi!

00:37:37.150 --> 00:37:39.621
-Tiffany.
-Peter, nice to meet you.

00:37:39.688 --> 00:37:41.849
We're just chilling watching baseball.

00:37:41.916 --> 00:37:44.695
-This is awesome.
-It's cool.

00:37:44.762 --> 00:37:47.484
-You got the old oak floors right?
-Yeah.

00:37:47.551 --> 00:37:49.602
These are all original wood floors.

00:37:49.669 --> 00:37:51.444
I think this was built in '57.

00:37:52.000 --> 00:37:54.250
-I'll show you the backyard.
-Congrats.

00:37:54.857 --> 00:37:56.355
-How's it feel?
-Good.

00:37:56.422 --> 00:37:57.481
-Awesome. [laughs]

00:37:58.375 --> 00:37:59.875
-Oh, nice man.

00:37:59.942 --> 00:38:03.001
-The rainy days
that we've had too are great in here.

00:38:03.450 --> 00:38:05.526
-You got a little sunroom out here.

00:38:05.593 --> 00:38:08.552
-I call it the rain room sometimes.
It's really nice.

00:38:08.619 --> 00:38:09.689
Yeah man.

00:38:09.756 --> 00:38:10.639
-This is…

00:38:11.360 --> 00:38:13.409
I've got a half acre lot.

00:38:13.854 --> 00:38:15.194
-Oh man.

00:38:15.261 --> 00:38:17.090
-You're winning here.
-Yeah man.

00:38:17.157 --> 00:38:20.320
Look what you can… get here.
It's crazy.

00:38:21.517 --> 00:38:23.730
Come back here and have coffee and relax.

00:38:24.875 --> 00:38:26.925
Listen to the birds. Everything's awesome.

00:38:26.992 --> 00:38:27.875
-Oh nice.

00:38:29.840 --> 00:38:32.507
This is all your land
all the way back to the A-frame?

00:38:32.574 --> 00:38:33.494
Past it.

00:38:33.561 --> 00:38:34.444
-Past it?
-Yeah.

00:38:36.241 --> 00:38:38.602
So I think actually this whole stretch here

00:38:38.669 --> 00:38:41.505
is some of the largest lots in Broadmoor.

00:38:42.102 --> 00:38:45.427
And this is one of the biggest backyards
in the whole neighborhood.

00:38:45.494 --> 00:38:46.979
-What's in the A-frame?

00:38:47.046 --> 00:38:49.363
It's just like
a little kid's hangout kind of.

00:38:49.430 --> 00:38:50.313
-Okay.

00:38:50.660 --> 00:38:52.016
You got a swing.

00:38:52.083 --> 00:38:54.083
-It's great. Yeah you got a little swing.

00:38:54.150 --> 00:38:55.796
-Oh, this is awesome.
-It is.

00:38:56.644 --> 00:38:59.526
You just come over here
and it's gorgeous up here.

00:39:00.683 --> 00:39:02.176
Peaceful, tranquil.

00:39:02.515 --> 00:39:04.613
I feel like I'm out of the city you know?

00:39:04.680 --> 00:39:08.130
Not everyone gets a yard like this
but a lot of the homes have a yard.

00:39:08.197 --> 00:39:09.566
-You grew up in Little Rock?

00:39:09.633 --> 00:39:10.953
Yeah. I call it home here.

00:39:11.020 --> 00:39:14.124
I grew up… My military family
when I was really young,

00:39:14.191 --> 00:39:16.970
this is where I've grown up.
I went to high school here.

00:39:17.037 --> 00:39:18.536
So this is home for me.

00:39:19.590 --> 00:39:20.719
[birds chirping]

00:39:23.460 --> 00:39:25.473
[Peter] You guys are gonna show us SoMa?

00:39:25.540 --> 00:39:27.490
Yeah I'll go show you around. Awesome.

00:39:27.557 --> 00:39:31.096
So homeownership here,
I feel like it's not only attainable

00:39:31.163 --> 00:39:34.582
to be achieved
and have that part of the American dream

00:39:34.649 --> 00:39:36.708
but you can do it and not feel like

00:39:37.406 --> 00:39:39.561
all of your money is going towards a home.

00:39:39.628 --> 00:39:42.205
We're still able to travel.
We're able to invest.

00:39:42.272 --> 00:39:43.453
We're not pinched.

00:39:43.520 --> 00:39:45.324
We have room to breathe.

00:39:46.391 --> 00:39:47.751
This is the start of SoMa.

00:39:47.818 --> 00:39:49.642
So the Southland Main District.

00:39:51.413 --> 00:39:53.197
-So this is like the hipster hood.

00:39:53.264 --> 00:39:56.809
It's like a artsy, youthful crowd here.

00:39:56.876 --> 00:39:59.122
Lots of great shops and restaurants.

00:39:59.189 --> 00:40:00.634
Lots of historic places too.

00:40:00.701 --> 00:40:03.289
We've got Community Bakery.
It's been there forever.

00:40:03.356 --> 00:40:06.326
Midtown Billiards up here
is an iconic bar in Little Rock.

00:40:06.393 --> 00:40:09.256
It's been here since
I think pre-World War II.

00:40:09.323 --> 00:40:12.568
Now they have big markets out here
and the parking lot.

00:40:12.635 --> 00:40:13.635
Got an art scene.

00:40:14.309 --> 00:40:16.336
So we're south of the line though.

00:40:16.403 --> 00:40:19.649
North of the line
was one Little Rock reality.

00:40:19.716 --> 00:40:21.498
South of the line, a different one.

00:40:21.565 --> 00:40:24.682
-But this is an exception?
-Oh I see what you're talking about.

00:40:24.749 --> 00:40:27.728
You're talking about how
the freeways have divided the city.

00:40:27.795 --> 00:40:28.846
-Yeah, exactly.

00:40:28.913 --> 00:40:31.619
Yeah, so I feel like originally this was

00:40:32.240 --> 00:40:34.251
predominantly wealthy,

00:40:34.730 --> 00:40:39.399
and then it changed a lot,
and then a lot of them moved out West,

00:40:40.072 --> 00:40:43.218
all of the changes
with the interstates came about

00:40:43.606 --> 00:40:46.013
and now it's starting to
come back and revitalize.

00:40:46.080 --> 00:40:49.993
-So how new is this? All this stuff
seems like it's pretty fresh.

00:40:50.060 --> 00:40:51.516
All the paint and everything.

00:40:51.583 --> 00:40:53.846
Yeah I'd say
all of these murals and stuff

00:40:53.913 --> 00:40:58.920
probably in the last
six, seven years at the latest.

00:40:58.987 --> 00:40:59.870
-Okay.

00:41:01.066 --> 00:41:03.379
It's cool seeing
these sort of underdog places.

00:41:03.446 --> 00:41:06.133
-I'd call Little Rock an underdog town.
-Yeah.

00:41:06.200 --> 00:41:07.675
It has more than you'd think.

00:41:07.742 --> 00:41:08.733
Yeah I do too.

00:41:08.800 --> 00:41:10.787
I think so and it's constantly

00:41:11.447 --> 00:41:14.503
you know, it's a thriving scene
for how small we are.

00:41:14.570 --> 00:41:16.443
Pettaway Square is farther down there

00:41:16.510 --> 00:41:18.773
and that's another area that's coming up.

00:41:18.840 --> 00:41:21.343
Okay what's your take?
The word gentrification.

00:41:21.410 --> 00:41:23.015
-Well…
-Or the effect of it.

00:41:23.650 --> 00:41:25.766
It's definitely a two-edged sword
you know.

00:41:25.833 --> 00:41:27.744
But I can't really feel like

00:41:28.200 --> 00:41:30.930
this is doing too much damage
in terms of SoMa's sense

00:41:30.997 --> 00:41:33.797
'cause I feel like
a lot of these neighborhoods over here

00:41:33.864 --> 00:41:38.122
were run down and there wasn't
a whole lot of people still really living

00:41:38.189 --> 00:41:40.650
in a lot of these areas
especially going towards…

00:41:40.717 --> 00:41:43.267
-Vacant home situation?
-A lot of vacant areas yeah.

00:41:43.334 --> 00:41:45.548
Lots and lots where homes
have been torn down

00:41:45.615 --> 00:41:48.119
and they're just
waiting for developers to come in.

00:41:48.186 --> 00:41:49.886
And now it's kind of all happened.

00:41:49.953 --> 00:41:52.143
People are moving into
this area all the time.

00:41:52.210 --> 00:41:55.714
I see it in so many cities
so it really depends who you ask.

00:41:56.300 --> 00:41:57.619
If someone owns a home

00:41:58.492 --> 00:42:01.419
in one of these places
that are getting gentrified

00:42:01.486 --> 00:42:03.226
they seem to be pretty happy.

00:42:03.293 --> 00:42:06.368
-Yeah.
-'Cause the value is ripping up.

00:42:06.435 --> 00:42:09.790
The homeowners that were living here,
the few that were still there,

00:42:09.857 --> 00:42:11.794
I'm sure they got paid pretty well.

00:42:11.861 --> 00:42:14.445
Most of them,
from my experience, seem to like it.

00:42:14.512 --> 00:42:17.313
And then who doesn't like a neighborhood
becoming safer?

00:42:17.380 --> 00:42:21.594
And that's the thing this neighborhood is
injecting a lot of youth to downtown again.

00:42:21.661 --> 00:42:25.132
And I think for a long time
Downtown Little Rock was kind of

00:42:25.729 --> 00:42:28.635
falling into a phase of getting left behind

00:42:28.702 --> 00:42:31.246
and everything was moving
out West towards Chenal.

00:42:31.313 --> 00:42:33.206
Out to the burbs where we were.

00:42:33.273 --> 00:42:36.077
And now things are coming back
to Downtown Little Rock.

00:42:36.144 --> 00:42:38.176
You know not just here on SoMa

00:42:38.243 --> 00:42:40.643
but on Main Street and downtown proper.

00:42:40.710 --> 00:42:42.493
It's kind of thriving a little bit.

00:42:42.560 --> 00:42:44.769
Who doesn't like gentrification?

00:42:44.836 --> 00:42:47.397
People that are living
in these places with low rent

00:42:47.464 --> 00:42:49.662
and then they're like oh sh*t.

00:42:49.728 --> 00:42:51.752
I mean there are sides to everything.

00:42:51.819 --> 00:42:53.978
-So double-edged sword.
-It always is.

00:42:54.045 --> 00:42:57.751
Like there's no clear answer
and it totally depends who you ask.

00:42:58.320 --> 00:43:01.381
But you can look around
and you see all the markets

00:43:01.448 --> 00:43:03.449
and it has its benefits.

00:43:05.154 --> 00:43:08.201
It's always been a favorite.
He's holding the pawn over here.

00:43:08.268 --> 00:43:09.959
He's not looking at it.

00:43:10.026 --> 00:43:12.346
And then over here looking at the king

00:43:12.413 --> 00:43:14.770
got the candle burning
like the light behind it.

00:43:14.837 --> 00:43:18.300
I feel like you can just be a pawn
and be like everything else

00:43:18.367 --> 00:43:20.804
or you can aim big and follow the light.

00:43:25.455 --> 00:43:28.458
[Hessam] See like these beautiful
turreted style homes.

00:43:28.525 --> 00:43:31.980
-People are coming in and renovating these
which is really awesome.

00:43:32.047 --> 00:43:34.975
-They don't make homes like these anymore.

00:43:35.042 --> 00:43:36.813
-[Peter] Victorian.
-Yeah.

00:43:36.880 --> 00:43:39.673
That's kind of the good side
of gentrification you know?

00:43:39.740 --> 00:43:42.820
A lot of these homes
have been collecting dust and vines

00:43:42.887 --> 00:43:43.853
and falling apart.

00:43:43.920 --> 00:43:46.310
-Yeah like that one's
fallen down over there.

00:43:46.377 --> 00:43:48.938
-People are coming in and completely
renovating them

00:43:49.005 --> 00:43:50.557
and saving them which is great.

00:43:50.624 --> 00:43:53.433
Keeping these beautiful historic homes.

00:43:53.500 --> 00:43:56.603
-So a lot of your friends you grew up with,

00:43:56.676 --> 00:43:58.695
do they stay around town or take off?

00:43:58.762 --> 00:44:02.856
-Both. It's the city where people grow up
and go on to other places.

00:44:02.923 --> 00:44:05.773
But then a lot of people
will also come back or stay here.

00:44:05.840 --> 00:44:09.087
I think it's both.
It satisfies two different angles there.

00:44:12.316 --> 00:44:14.254
-[woman] One step.
-[man] One step?

00:44:14.343 --> 00:44:15.755
-Go like this.
-Yeah.

00:44:15.822 --> 00:44:16.853
Yeah, all right.

00:44:16.920 --> 00:44:19.359
[camera shutter clicks]

00:44:23.869 --> 00:44:24.752
Good?

00:44:25.417 --> 00:44:26.639
Let me see.

00:44:27.932 --> 00:44:29.545
[Peter] Oh there you go. Nice.

00:44:30.390 --> 00:44:31.818
Graduated high school?

00:44:31.885 --> 00:44:33.826
-I'm finna' graduate.

00:44:35.384 --> 00:44:37.593
-Nice.
What about your buddy over here?

00:44:37.660 --> 00:44:38.711
I'm younger than him.

00:44:38.778 --> 00:44:40.123
-You look older.

00:44:40.190 --> 00:44:41.582
That what everybody say!

00:44:41.649 --> 00:44:42.752
He my older brother.

00:44:42.819 --> 00:44:45.054
I'm in the 12th grade and he's 11th.

00:44:46.020 --> 00:44:48.023
-Alright alright. Good stuff guys.

00:44:49.098 --> 00:44:52.023
We're gonna add a superhero
like Superman.

00:44:52.090 --> 00:44:55.455
I see that. I can see that.
She's got a good creative eye.

00:44:55.522 --> 00:44:58.051
She's bringing it out of you. See you guys.

00:44:58.730 --> 00:45:00.880
[Peter] Alright Hessam,
good tour today man.

00:45:00.947 --> 00:45:02.233
We saw a lot.

00:45:02.300 --> 00:45:05.603
Above the line, below the line,
everything in between the line,

00:45:05.670 --> 00:45:08.177
and now we're back
to the starting point basically.

00:45:08.244 --> 00:45:10.383
-Thank you for that.
-It's been a pleasure.

00:45:10.449 --> 00:45:12.149
It's nice to have you in our city.

00:45:12.216 --> 00:45:14.812
I love seeing the pride of your city.

00:45:14.893 --> 00:45:17.552
I'm trying to do more videos
with younger people.

00:45:17.970 --> 00:45:20.207
And you're making your dreams happen.

00:45:20.274 --> 00:45:22.983
Darren, who we just met,
is making his dream happen.

00:45:23.696 --> 00:45:26.351
That woman,
I forget her name, wisdom bombs.

00:45:26.418 --> 00:45:27.771
She's making it happen.

00:45:28.317 --> 00:45:29.703
And I love seeing that.

00:45:30.295 --> 00:45:32.574
Little Rock was
a big surprise for me as well.

00:45:32.641 --> 00:45:35.399
First time other than
when I dropped here for 30 minutes

00:45:35.466 --> 00:45:37.794
but quite impressive from what I saw.

00:45:37.861 --> 00:45:39.248
Awesome. Glad you enjoyed.

00:45:39.315 --> 00:45:42.849
And guys,
part of an Arkansas series.

00:45:43.297 --> 00:45:46.760
I think I'm gonna do five videos
in total from Arkansas.

00:45:47.487 --> 00:45:50.546
If you like this,
the next one, I'm going to Pine Bluff.

00:45:51.794 --> 00:45:53.509
Which is a different reality.

00:45:53.576 --> 00:45:55.720
And then going up to Bentonville,

00:45:55.787 --> 00:45:58.146
which is totally different
from what I've heard.

00:45:58.213 --> 00:46:01.715
-Totally different.
-Ozarks, Delta, all over the state.

00:46:01.782 --> 00:46:03.997
Alright you guys,
thanks for coming on that journey.

00:46:04.064 --> 00:46:05.344
Until the next one.

00:46:05.411 --> 00:46:07.382
[jazz music]

